# ==========================================
# BINANCE API CONFIGURATION - DUAL SETUP
# ==========================================

# 1. PRODUCTION API (for realtime market data)
#    Used by: Data Fetcher (for CHoCH signal detection)
#    Purpose: Fetch real market data (OHLCV, prices, volume)
#    Source: Production Binance API
BINANCE_API_KEY=your_production_api_key_here
BINANCE_SECRET=your_production_secret_here

# 2. DEMO/TESTNET API (for trading/order execution)
#    Used by: Trading Exchange (for position management)
#    Purpose: Execute orders safely on testnet
#    Source: Binance Futures Testnet
#    Get testnet keys from: https://testnet.binancefuture.com
#    NOTE: If not set, will fallback to main BINANCE_API_KEY
BINANCE_API_KEY_DEMO=your_testnet_api_key_here
BINANCE_SECRET_DEMO=your_testnet_secret_here

# ==========================================
# DUAL EXCHANGE EXPLANATION
# ==========================================
# This system uses TWO separate exchange instances:
#
# Instance 1: REALTIME DATA FETCHER
#   - Uses: BINANCE_API_KEY / BINANCE_SECRET
#   - Purpose: Fetch market data for CHoCH detection
#   - Source: ALWAYS production (real market data)
#   - Controlled by: USE_REALTIME_DATA (default=1)
#
# Instance 2: DEMO/LIVE TRADING EXCHANGE
#   - Uses: BINANCE_API_KEY_DEMO / BINANCE_SECRET_DEMO
#   - Purpose: Execute orders & manage positions
#   - Source: Testnet (demo) or Production (live)
#   - Controlled by: DEMO_TRADING (1=testnet, 0=production)
#
# Why separate? To analyze REAL market data while trading 
# safely on testnet without risking real money.
# ==========================================

